pageContext.claim: “We brought back more than $300 billion worth of deals [from Asia], which could reach well over a trillion dollars within a very near future. That means jobs for the United States at a very high level.”
pageContext.analysis: This is not accurate. Many of the arrangements are non-binding memorandums rather than legal contracts, valued at $250 billion. Still, it remains to be seen if the initial contracts will come to fruition -- and it's probably fantasy that the deals will grow in value to $1 trillion. And despite the claims of success, the trade deficit with China has grown 7 percent from January to October, according to a December report from the Commerce Department.
